cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.IR, cs.NE 

This paper deals with natural language processing and machine learning techniques for detecting lexical semantic change. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also involves the use of machine learning models, which suggests that it could be categorized under cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper involves the use of algorithms to induce semantic change, which could fall under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also involves the use of evaluation metrics, which suggests that it could be categorized under cs.IR (Information Retrieval). Finally, the paper involves the use of large-scale datasets, which could fall under cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
